                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Catalogue no. 11; Nelson collection no. N265.  Teos, son of Petenephotes is Muhs&amp;apos; Taxpayer 8.  The scribe Paches was responsible for several other yoke tax receipts and perhaps one nehet-tax receipt from Thebes between years 11 and 16, probably of Ptolemy II.  (See additional OIM ostraca.)</note>
